Creating and Managing Models

Models are created via /api/describe, NOT /api/data.

Create a model:
  curl -X POST -d '[{"model_name":"products","description":"..."}]' /api/describe/models

Create fields for a model:
  curl -X POST -d '[{"model_name":"products","field_name":"name","type":"text","required":true}]' /api/describe/fields

Field types: text, integer, decimal, boolean, date, datetime, reference, jsonb

Common field options:
  required: true/false
  unique: true/false
  description: "Field description"

Reference fields (foreign keys):
  type: "reference"
  related_model: "other_model"
  relationship_type: "many_to_one"

Example - create products model with fields:
  curl -X POST -d '[{"model_name":"products","description":"Product catalog"}]' /api/describe/models
  curl -X POST -d '[
    {"model_name":"products","field_name":"name","type":"text","required":true},
    {"model_name":"products","field_name":"sku","type":"text","required":true,"unique":true},
    {"model_name":"products","field_name":"status","type":"text","required":true}
  ]' /api/describe/fields

View model schema:
  describe products
